<paragraph id="DB05E35F09145B285490E2E6E74AFAC7" blockId="9.[151,1437,461,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09145B285490E2E6E475FB36" box="[197,299,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species can be easily distinguished from the other species of 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09145B285000E2E6E1F5FB36" box="[1109,1195,1221,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09145B285000E2E6E1F5FB36" box="[1109,1195,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Cofana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its external dark brown coloration and the shape of the aedeagal shaft that is broadly flattened, triangular, with spiny projections along the posterior margin.
</paragraph>
